  m_text: "B\xE1nh m\xEC is a popular Vietnamese street food made with a baguette
    filled with meats, vegetables, and sauces. It is commonly eaten as a quick and
    filling meal because it is easy to carry around. The dish was influenced by French
    colonial history and later adapted with Vietnamese ingredients. Common ingredients
    include pickled carrots, cucumber, cilantro, chili, and different types of pork
    or chicken. \r\n"
